cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.SY, cs.GR, cs.NI

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper proposes a Simultaneous Localization and Mapping (SLAM) algorithm for urban navigation using GPS and fish-eye camera. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper addresses data association errors in pixel intensities across image frames and proposes a superpixel-based piecewise Random Sample Consensus (RANSAC) technique to perform spatial voting across image pixels. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper uses vehicle dynamics to perform graph optimization and estimate the fault mode vector. 
- cs.GR (Graphics): The paper uses a fish-eye camera to capture images for navigation. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper uses satellite ephemeris data for graph optimization.
